article.headline: Quinnipiac 71, Wagner 63
article.story: EDS: APNewsNow. Quinnipiac 71, Wagner 63. NEW YORK -- James Feldeine had 19 points and 10 rebounds to lead Quinnipiac to a 71-63 victory over Wagner on Saturday night. Bryan Geffen added 15 points and Justin Rutty had 14 for the Bobcats (5-3, 2-0 Northeast Conference). Llew Radford led the Seahawks (5-3, 0-1) with 17 points, while Joey Mundweiler had 12 and Michael Orock 11. Quinnipiac took the lead for good on a layup by Rutty with 10:14 left that made it 43-42. The Bobcats' biggest lead was 67-59 on a 3-pointer by DeAndre Bynum with 1:25 to play.
